abstract: National Assn of Realtors says sales of existing homes rose 3.2 percent in June 2015 to seasonally adjusted annual rate of 5.49 million, highest since February 2007.
lead_paragraph: Sales of existing homes rose 3.2 percent last month to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 5.49 million, the highest rate since February 2007

headline.main: Home Sales Jump in June as Demand Exceeds Supply
